(thirdQuint)Visual Reconstitution Therapy After Optic Neuritis.

 Patients with an acute optic neuritis (between 60 and 180 days before screening) or with residual visual deficits after a past optic neuritis are randomized in two treatment groups.

 Group A is instructed to perform software-based visual reconstitution therapy on a home PC daily and regularly for 30 minutes over a period of six month.

 Group B will perform a similarly, also software-based training program, developed to improve saccadic eye movements rather than visual fields.

 Patients are blinded to the respective treatment.

